text:
How is everyone so convinced that innovating on the core protocol level is wrong? I am speaking about #Bitcoin and #Ethereum especially.

People are throwing around worlds why scaling is not working, why sharding is not working, without actually trying at least to think hardly about that. Proof of this, proof of that, data availability, ZK this and that, fraud proofs or not.

So many excuses, while in the current L2 space everything is accepted. Multisig of 2 out of 3. Centralised sequencers. KYC chain. Censorship. Centralisation. Fragmentation of users, wallets, liquidity.

So in the 15 years since blockchain is a thing, writing excuses and convincing people that these excuses are valid is the game. This is the narrative. While there are so many hardcore developers who really care, who really see a better way, they demonstrate and work towards higher goals.

Sharding works for a few chains already EGLD, NEAR, TON, Radix, and probably a few more. No downtime, composability solved, collusion solved, validity solved.

All the problems Ethereum/EVM has because of its design choices might not be a problem on other systems as the design is different. Like Native assets vs ERC tokens. Or one Patricia Merkle Trie per account vs only one global trie.

Every problem has a solution, it is engineering, it is hard, but that makes it fun. Really. Trying out different solutions and making it work. No compromises, just make it work.

The space is fighting inside so much that those coming from the outside just don't understand. The space is not attracting enough talents because it is so divided. AI took a lot of talents, because AI is innovating. They actually rewrite the basic principles every 3-4 years and they are not afraid of doing so.

We need to change the game. We need to accelerate and you can accelerate only when you start to understand your problems and you start to implement solutions for that. One step a time, but as fast as possible.

The debate between #Ethereum and #Solana was so and so. Some talking points here and there, but it is quite maddening as well. 

Like some facts were completely wrong: there is no interconnected seamless state machine experience in Ethereum and there is noone clearly building this.

Some research here and there, some would say it is the same as in 2018 when sharding was the top priority, but it was never delivered. Still researchers thinking about how dApp from X L2 can read state from Y L2. Just why?

I know the answer, as they still think about ERC SC based token systems, where you would need to read and execute on the SC only. Actually you can‚Äôt scale ERC tokens, those will be always dependent on a single state. You will need to wrap and create multiple SC contracts to scale.

Also, it is super nice that Solana makes a case for scaling, however with better engineering you can have the same/more execution speed with inexpensive machines. I would not want to bet on constant hardware scaling, when it is possible to have software scaling.

If you want interconnected seamless experience, you can find it on #MultiversX which uses sharding, novel consensus mechanism, the fastest execution environment: SpaceVM and tons of more innovation.

If you want interconnected L2 experience, build on #SovereignChain SDK to use all the innovations of the mainchain, with native assets, seamless composability with MultiversX dApps and integrated native cross chain operations with various L1s.

Build where it matters, what it matters.

Just build it!
